# cppcheck suppressions for the report-only CI static-analysis job.
# One-off false positives are suppressed inline at the source with
# `// cppcheck-suppress <id>`; this file holds the project-wide, intentional
# patterns so the report stays signal-rich. Keep it small — prefer fixing a
# finding or an inline suppression over adding a blanket entry here.

# Vendored third-party code (cpp-httplib, nlohmann/json, miniz, ...). The CI's
# `-i mxbmrp3/vendor` only drops vendor files from the CHECK LIST — a vendor header
# still gets analysed when OUR code #includes it (e.g. http_server.cpp -> httplib.h),
# so findings inside it leak into the report. We don't patch vendored code (it's a
# drop-in from upstream, tracked in vendored.json), so scope it out by path too. (Seen:
# httplib.h ChunkedDecoder::line_buf `uninitMemberVar` — a std::string member that
# self-initialises; a false positive anyway.)
*:mxbmrp3/vendor/*

# Widgets/HUDs call the virtual rebuildRenderData() from their own constructor by
# design. The call resolves to the leaf class being constructed (which is exactly
# the intent), so the "dynamic binding is not used" gotcha does not apply here.
virtualCallInConstructor

# HUD subclasses intentionally redeclare a few members/accessors that also exist
# on BaseHud (public configuration data the settings UI touches directly — a
# documented design decision, see CLAUDE.md "Public member variables on HUDs").
duplInheritedMember

# Several render paths initialise two locals (e.g. currentColor/peakColor,
# textColor/iconColor) to the same value on purpose; they diverge conditionally
# below. Not a copy-paste bug.
duplicateAssignExpression

# steam_friends_manager wraps every Steamworks call in SEH_TRY/SEH_EXCEPT_ALL
# (__try/__except) with a return in both branches. cppcheck can't see through the
# SEH macros and thinks a path falls off the end.
missingReturn:mxbmrp3/core/steam_friends_manager.cpp

# http_server prints 32-bit ids/hashes with %x; the args are `unsigned long`,
# which is 32-bit on the Windows (LLP64) target, so %x is correct there. cppcheck
# flags it as a type mismatch regardless of platform.
invalidPrintfArgType_uint:mxbmrp3/core/http_server.cpp
